-- Spain's Liberbank sells shares at 0.85 euros each
-- 
-- Thu May 22, 2014 03:00AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, May 22 (Reuters) - Spain's Liberbank <LBK.MC> said on Thursday it had sold 372.69 million shares in the market at 0.85 euros ($1.16) each, raising about 317 million euros via a placement of new and old shares in the first phase of a capital-boosting effort.

Liberbank, granted state aid during the country's property and banking crisis, said that of the total number of shares sold, 117.65 mln were newly issued.